<subSubSection id="572ED3BE09A1CB7FFBE321749203381F" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FE57B1CFD43F03133734A758D935E12F" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC455D428BBCFB0A458EABE64CF60027" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Members of 
<taxonomicName id="D1E5E174F1023FF24F0763A485D57980" authorityName="Mercado" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster albopilosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albopilosus">
<emphasis id="6C246943F2B671D77661A2BD116394E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster albopilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the combination of the following characters: body 3.5-5.5 mm; fore wing entirely infuscate with dark stigma; fore tibia pale; mid and hind femur entirely dark; T2 entirely dark.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
